# React Native Theming Rules

## CRITICAL PERFORMANCE RULE

The `themed()` function creates NEW style objects on every call (`Object.assign({}, ...stylesArray)` in theme context). Using it inline in JSX can cause unnecessary re-renders and component remounting issues like TextInput losing focus.

**Default approach: Use static styles. Only use themed() when you need dynamic theme values.**

## Style Definitions Priority

### 1. Static Styles (PREFERRED)

Use plain React Native style objects for styles that don't need theme-aware values:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Static, stable references
const $container: ViewStyle = {
  flex: 1,
  padding: 16,
  backgroundColor: "#667eea",
}

const $title: TextStyle = {
  fontSize: 24,
  fontWeight: "600",
  color: "white",
}

const $input: TextStyle = {
  color: "white",
  fontSize: 16,
  fontFamily: "System",
  flex: 1,
}
```

**When to use static styles:**
- Styles with fixed values (colors, sizes, spacing)
- Components with TextInput or other focus-sensitive elements
- Any component that re-renders frequently
- Animated components where style stability matters
- Forms and interactive elements

### 2. ThemedStyle Functions (USE SPARINGLY)

Only use when you ACTUALLY need:
- Dynamic colors based on light/dark mode
- Theme spacing tokens that change
- Typography that varies by theme

```typescript
import type { ThemedStyle } from "@/theme/types";

const $container: ThemedStyle<ViewStyle> = ({ spacing, colors, isDark }) => ({
  padding: spacing.md,
  backgroundColor: isDark ? colors.palette.neutral900 : colors.palette.neutral100,
});

const $text: ThemedStyle<TextStyle> = ({ typography, colors }) => ({
  fontFamily: typography.primary.normal,
  color: colors.text,
});
```

### 3. Memoize themed() Calls When Required

If you must use themed() for specific elements, memoize the result to prevent recreating objects:

```typescript
import { useMemo } from "react";

const containerStyle = useMemo(() => themed($container), [themed])
const textStyle = useMemo(() => themed($text), [themed])

<View style={containerStyle}>
  <Text style={textStyle}>Content</Text>
</View>
```

## Applying Styles

### Static Styles (Preferred)

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Direct reference, no re-renders
<View style={$container}>
  <Text style={$title}>Title</Text>
  <TextInput style={$input} value={text} onChangeText={setText} />
</View>
```

### Themed Styles (Only When Needed)

```typescript
// ⚠️ USE SPARINGLY - Creates new objects on every render
<View style={themed($container)}>
  <Text style={themed($heading)} />
</View>

// ✅ BETTER - Memoize to prevent recreation
const containerStyle = useMemo(() => themed($dynamicContainer), [themed])
<View style={containerStyle}>
```

### Combining Multiple Styles

```typescript
// Static styles
<View style={[$container, $centered]} />

// Mixed static and themed (memoize the themed part)
const themedStyle = useMemo(() => themed($dynamicContainer), [themed])
<View style={[$staticBase, themedStyle]} />
```

### Direct Theme Access

For single values, access theme directly instead of using themed():

```typescript
const { theme } = useAppTheme();

<Image
  source={logo}
  tintColor={theme.colors.palette.neutral900}
/>
```

## Migration Pattern

When converting from themed() to static:

```typescript
// ❌ Before (causes re-renders, TextInput loses focus)
const $input: ThemedStyle<TextStyle> = ({ typography }) => ({
  fontSize: 16,
  fontFamily: typography.primary.normal,
  color: "white",
})
<TextInput style={themed($input)} />

// ✅ After (stable reference)
const $input: TextStyle = {
  fontSize: 16,
  fontFamily: "System",
  color: "white",
}
<TextInput style={$input} />
```

## When themed() is Actually Needed

Use themed() ONLY for:

1. **Dark mode color switching** - Background/text colors that change with theme
2. **Dynamic spacing** - When using theme spacing tokens (spacing.md, spacing.lg)
3. **Typography variants** - When using theme typography definitions
4. **Components that don't re-render frequently** - Static screens, headers

**Do NOT use themed() for:**
- TextInput components or their containers
- Form elements that update frequently
- Animated components
- Any component with fixed colors/sizes

## Style Naming Convention

- Prefix all style constants with `$`
- Use camelCase for style names
- Be descriptive: `$container`, `$title`, `$submitButton`
- Add `Static` prefix when mixing approaches: `$staticInput`, `$staticWrapper`

## Common Patterns

### TextInput Components (Always Static)

```typescript
// Always use static styles for inputs and their containers
const $inputWrapper: ViewStyle = {
  width: "100%",
  height: 56,
  backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)",
  borderRadius: 12,
  paddingHorizontal: 16,
  justifyContent: "center",
}

const $input: TextStyle = {
  color: "white",
  fontSize: 16,
  fontFamily: "System",
  flex: 1,
}

<View style={$inputWrapper}>
  <TextInput
    style={$input}
    value={email}
    onChangeText={setEmail}
  />
</View>
```

### Theme-Aware Containers (Memoized)

```typescript
// Only if colors MUST change with theme
const { themed } = useAppTheme();

const containerStyle = useMemo(() => themed($container), [themed])

<View style={containerStyle}>
  <Text>Content</Text>
</View>
```

### Mixed Approach (Static Base + Dynamic Colors)

```typescript
// Static structure
const $button: ViewStyle = {
  height: 56,
  borderRadius: 12,
  justifyContent: "center",
  alignItems: "center",
  paddingHorizontal: 16,
}

// Add theme-aware background (memoized)
const { theme } = useAppTheme();
const buttonStyle = useMemo(() => ({
  ...$button,
  backgroundColor: theme.colors.primary,
}), [theme.colors.primary])

<Pressable style={buttonStyle}>
  <Text>Submit</Text>
</Pressable>
```

### Entire Screen with Static Styles

```typescript
export const LoginScreen: FC = () => {
  const [email, setEmail] = useState("")
  
  return (
    <View style={$container}>
      <View style={$cardContent}>
        <Text style={$title}>Welcome</Text>
        <View style={$inputWrapper}>
          <TextInput
            style={$input}
            value={email}
            onChangeText={setEmail}
          />
        </View>
        <Pressable style={$button}>
          <Text style={$buttonText}>Continue</Text>
        </Pressable>
      </View>
    </View>
  )
}

// All styles are static - stable references
const $container: ViewStyle = {
  flex: 1,
  backgroundColor: "#667eea",
}

const $cardContent: ViewStyle = {
  padding: 32,
  gap: 16,
}

const $title: TextStyle = {
  fontSize: 28,
  fontWeight: "600",
  color: "white",
  textAlign: "center",
}

const $inputWrapper: ViewStyle = {
  height: 56,
  backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)",
  borderRadius: 12,
  paddingHorizontal: 16,
}

const $input: TextStyle = {
  fontSize: 16,
  color: "white",
  flex: 1,
}

const $button: ViewStyle = {
  height: 56,
  backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3)",
  borderRadius: 16,
  justifyContent: "center",
  alignItems: "center",
}

const $buttonText: TextStyle = {
  fontSize: 16,
  fontWeight: "500",
  color: "white",
}
```

## Theme Object Properties

When you do need ThemedStyle functions, they receive:

- `spacing`: Spacing scale (xs, sm, md, lg, xl, xxl, etc.)
- `colors`: Color palette and semantic colors
  - `colors.palette.neutral100`, `colors.palette.neutral900`, etc.
  - Other palette colors as defined in theme
- `typography`: Typography definitions (fonts, sizes, line heights, etc.)
- `timing`: Animation timing values
- `isDark`: Boolean indicating if dark theme is currently active

**Example with all properties:**

```typescript
const $container: ThemedStyle<ViewStyle> = ({
  spacing,
  colors,
  typography,
  timing,
  isDark,
}) => ({
  padding: spacing.md,
  backgroundColor: isDark
    ? colors.palette.neutral900
    : colors.palette.neutral100,
});
```

## Shared Styles

Import common reusable styles from `@/theme/styles`:

```typescript
import { $styles } from "@/theme/styles"

<Screen preset="fixed" contentContainerStyle={$styles.flex1} />
```

## Performance Checklist

Before using themed():

- [ ] Does this style actually need theme values?
- [ ] Can I use fixed colors/sizes instead?
- [ ] Is this a TextInput or form component? (use static)
- [ ] Does this component re-render frequently? (use static)
- [ ] If I must use themed(), am I memoizing it?

**Remember: Static styles are faster, simpler, and prevent bugs. Use themed() only when absolutely necessary.**
